reviewText:
I enjoyed playing it; it was like underwater minecraft except with a sizeable amount less features. For the price I paid though that seems fair ($4 on sale).

The developer has mentioned that they're not going to be working on the game any further, so what you see is what you get. It's a bit unfortunate since there could be some simple changes that would make the gameplay better, but I understand the dev's reasoning (first time home-brewed 3d java engine has its limitations).

@Dev: I wish there was a way to sleep the dangerous night away, and an ability for me to mark waypoints on the mini-map so I wouldn't get lost so much.
